.TH man 1 "15 april 2020" "0.32" "simple_shell man page"
.SH NAME
.B simple_shell 
- UNIX command interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
[command [flags]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The command interpreter simple_shell is a Sub-shell that after of compiled all your files ".c" and then executing, takes keyboard commands and passes them to the operating system to carry out.
.Lp 
Its process starts by checking if a file descriptor refers to a terminal, then proceeds to display the prompt ($) while waiting for a command to be entered
The command is read and stored in a buffer then divided to be returned as an array. The array in its initial position is compared with the exit command.
.LP
Then it is evaluated if it is interactive or non-interactive, after this a child process is created with the fork function to execute the input command 
.Lp
Use waitpid function to wait for state changes in the child of the calling process and obtein information about of child.
.SH RETURN VALUE
Return the exection in standard output of the command typed by the user if the command doesnÂ´t exist menssage error.
.SH EXAMPLE
One of the most common uses is with the 
.LP
.B $ls
.LP
lists all files and directories in the current directory is ls, which is short for list.
.LP
.B $ls -l
.LP
we will get all the files and directories of the current directory, in long format.
.SH SEE ALSO
.I fork, execve, exit, fflush, free, getline, isatty, stat, strtok, wait, waitpid
